        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>&#34;Jerusalem &#40;Holy City&#41; the Glory of all Lands.&#34;¬ù<lb/>
                ALFRED A. MARCUS&#44;<lb/>
                Diamond Merchant and Importer&#44;<lb/>
                Purchaser of Real Estate&#44; &#40;Landed Property.&#41;<lb/>
                Residence&#44; 127 DARTMOUTH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>No business will be transacted or interviews had on the Jewish Sabbath&#44; from one hour before sunset on<lb/> Friday until one hour after sunset on Saturday&#44; or on the Jewish Festivals&#44; and no letters will be opened on<lb/> those days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Boston&#44; Sivan 25<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5641<lb/></p>
            <p>Revd S. Morais<lb/>
                My beloved friend<lb/></p>
            <p>I hereby authorise you to say to<lb/> your congregation on behalf of my beloved<lb/> wife daughter &#38; son.  That we will pay off<lb/> the entire <sic>indebtness</sic> of your shule within<lb/> three months form this date upon the<lb/> following conditions.<lb/></p>
            <p>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi>. That the shule synagogue shall<lb/> never again upon or on any conditions<lb/> ever again be mortgaged.<lb/></p>
            <p>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>. That there never shall upon any<lb/> terms or conditions ever any other but<lb/> the strictest orthodox ritual ever be<lb/> introduced into the shule.<lb/></p>
            <p>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>. Any person whose means will not<lb/> allow them shall be refused a seat if<lb/> possibly on any festivals or Sabbath.<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. That on the Anniversary of the death of<lb/> my beloved <sic>&#38;</sic> wife parents &#38; also Lady<lb/> Judith Montefore wife of Sire Moses<lb/> Montefore prayers be <sic>mad</sic> in their<lb/> memory.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>&#38; further any such suggestions for the<lb/> good &#38; well conducting of schools &#38;<lb/> <sic>&#38;</sic> synagogue you may recommend<lb/> shall be carried out.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>I should be glad if you will inform<lb/> me the amt of <sic>indebtness</sic>.  Of course<lb/> any member of <hi rend="underline">orthodox</hi> principals<lb/> who is anxious to donate with me I<lb/> not object but <hi rend="underline">do not wish any assistance<lb/> from others</hi><lb/></p>
            <p>Yours most faithfully<lb/>
                Alfred A Marcus<lb/></p>
            <p>Will also send<lb/> a scroll of Law &#38;<lb/> Silver as a witness<lb/> if they agree to<lb/> alone to be<lb/> kept in<lb/> shul<lb/> on<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93;<lb/></p>
        </body>
